  "text": "Equation (19) reveals the connection between a multiple testing problem and an FDR estimation problem. The BH procedure and adaptive p-value procedure can be identified as special cases in the class. For example, if we chooseˆ n = 0 andĜ(t) as the empirical CDF, then (19) reduces to the well-known BH procedure. [CITATION_1] developed a stochastic process framework for multiple testing and showed that, when consistent estimates of G and p are chosen, the class of plug-in procedures (19) are asymptotically valid and exhaustive. That is, the FDR is controlled at level α + o(1).",
