      "span_text": "For example, if we chooseˆ n = 0 andĜ(t) as the empirical CDF, then (19) reduces to the well-known BH procedure. developed a stochastic process framework for multiple testing and showed that, when consistent estimates of G and p are chosen, the class of plug-in procedures (19) are asymptotically valid and exhaustive."
